Virtue? a fig! 'tis in ourselves that we are thus or thgus, Our bodies are our gardens, to the which our wills are gardeners. ... If the balance of our lives had not one scale of reason to poise another of sensuality, the blood and baseness of our natures would conduct us to most preopoosterous conclusions, But we have reason to cool our raging motions, our carnal stings, our unbitted lusts.
