Most potetnt, grave and revered signoirs... 
... Rude am I in my speech
And little blessed with the soft phrase of peace,
For since these arms of mine hav sven years' pith
Till now some nie moons wasted, they have used
Their deares action in the tented field'
And little of this great world can I speak
More than pertains to feats of broil and battle; And therefore little shall I grace my cause
In speaking for myself. UYet by your gracious patiensce,
 will a round unvarnished tale deliver
Of my whole course of love...
-Othello

